{
  "stem": "14060.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 1.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "However, as in every community, there are people who are not prepared to pay up.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And usually the more they have, the less they pay.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was this problem.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Whilst the mainstream paid up, because one didn't want to-- people presumably didn't want to be put to shame that they didn't pay-- and they had the right of appeal, by the way, for the amount they were assessed.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, you know, they could bring their income tax returns.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They could bring an inspection of the stocks of goods and approximate turnover.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So it was really like an audit of the business if anybody wished to dispute the amount they were asked for.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So it wasn't a free-for-all.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, it was relatively in an orderly, justifiable true fashion conducted.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now the interesting part was, obviously, there is always the odd person who doesn't pay.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So what do you do with them?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, the-- my father was all the years in the Orthodox community that I remember the head of the chevra kadisha, which is the burial society.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In fact, I have a very interesting photo which I cannot put my hands on, that it was customary for the chevra kadisha to hold an annual [NON-ENGLISH], a celebration, on the seventh of Adar, which is Moshe Rabbenu's [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there used to be a nice, catered party given.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the custom in our town was that the members of the committee of the chevra kadisha-- obviously they were there, they led the whole proceedings-- turned up in a white kittel.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, this is the white gown which you use on Yom Kippur or some-- we did it on Rosh Hashanah and on seder night, the person who gives the seder.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
